FT  17 FEB 94 / Bavarian right-winger resigns
A leading German opponent of European union, Bavarian environment minister
Mr Peter Gauweiler, resigned yesterday over a financial scandal, Reuter
reports from Bonn.
His Christian Social Union party was embarrassed by revelations that the
populist Mr Gauweiler,44, had earned DM10,000 (Pounds 3,891) a month on top
of his political salaries by 'leasing' clients from his law firm to other
attorneys.
